NOXOLO MIYA noxolo.miya@inl.co.za Johannesburg - South African singer and record producer Zakes Bantwini, real name Zakhele Madida, lost his father, Sihlangusihle Jeffrey Khanyile, last week. The 65-year-old Khanyile succumbed to his death on January 4, and the musician's wife, Nandi Madida, posted a heartfelt message on her Instagram and shared a heartfelt tribute about the passing of her father-in-law and condolences to her husband. Madida said: “I am eternally grateful by the kindness you showed me as your daughter-in-law, you truly made me feel like your daughter in love. “You had a wicked sense of humour that we will miss dearly, thank you for making me feel like family and welcoming me so warmly. You are with your creator now. “Thank you once again, I am eternally grateful. Love and thoughts are with my husband, family and all your loved ones during this very difficult time.” According to another statement released by the family, Bantwini's father died on last Wednesday night around 9pm at his homestead in Nkandla, north of KwaZulu-Natal. “He was 65 years old at the time of his untimely death. Mr Khanyile leaves behind his wife and nine children. “We are devastated by the loss of our father," said his children in a joint statement. “We will miss his sense of humour, his resilience and how he always made sure we follow our culture. He will be deeply missed for his kindness and loving nature,” said the statement. The family asked for prayers and privacy during this difficult time. Several artists and celebrities have also conveyed their messages of condolences for Bantwini. The Star